[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Pagebanner default.jpg"],["unesco=yes"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Trier Porta Nigra BW 1.JPG"],["300px"],["thumb"],["The Porta Nigra"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.trier-info.de\/english\/index Trier"]}]}," on the banks of the Moselle, in the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rhineland-Palatinate"]]}," region of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Germany"]]},", is the country's oldest city, dating from Roman times. Today it has 105,600 inhabitants.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\nTrier is rich in ruins from the Roman Empire (protected by ",{"type":"[[","value":[["UNESCO World Heritage List"],["UNESCO"]]},"), such as the Porta Nigra, the Roman baths and Roman amphitheater.\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Trier - Aula Palatina.JPG"],["thumbnail"],["Basilica of Constantine"]]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By plane"]},"\nThere are several airports in the vicinity with reasonable access to Trier.\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Luxembourg#By plane"],["Luxembourg Airport"]]}," is about 50 km away."]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" Low-cost carrier hub ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hahn"],["Frankfurt-Hahn"]]}," is 75 km east of Trier.  There are roughly-hourly Flibco buses, but the bus stop is several km out of town near the Nell's Park hotel. This airport is also reachable ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.airportshuttle-mosel.de\/AirportHahn\/ by bus"]}," from Bullay in 51 minutes, which can be reached using IC trains (34 minutes from Trier Hbf)."]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Frankfurt"]]}," International Airport is about 210 km away. The train from there would be about 3 hours via ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Saarbrücken"]]}," or ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Koblenz"]]},"."]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By train"]},"\nTrains leave hourly from ",{"type":"{{","value":[["marker"],["type=listing"],["name=Trier Hbf"],["lat=49.757039"],["long=6.651877"],["url=http:\/\/www.bahnhof.de\/bahnhof-de\/Trier_Hbf.html"]]}," to Saarbrücken, Koblenz and Cologne. Timetable and ticket information can be found at ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.bahn.de\/i\/view\/GBR\/en\/index.shtml Deutsche Bahn"]},".\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By car"]},"\nTrier is connected by the European motorway E44 from Luxembourg city (~50 km) via Trier to Koblenz (~100 km), E422 from Trier to Saarbrücken (~100 km).\n\nTrier is connected to the Autobahn A6.  This city is about one hour from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kaiserslautern"]]}," or two hours from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mannheim"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By boat"]},"\nThere are some cruise trips from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Koblenz"]]}," to Trier. However, they are expensive.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\nWalking is the best way to travel around the city, though a vehicle is good when visiting the stadium.  Also there is a scenic overview up the hill by the stadium where you can see the entire city.  The city tours take you up there.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Trier Roman amphitheatre in October 2011.JPG"],["right"],["thumb"],["250px"],["Roman Amphitheatre"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Trier Dom BW 24.JPG"],["thumb"],["250px"],["Trier Cathedral"]]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Porta Nigra"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.trier-info.de\/english\/porta-nigra-info"],["email="],["address=Porta-Nigra-Platz"],["lat=49.759645"],["long=6.644064"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Build between 186 and 200 AD this is the largest Roman city gate still standing north of the Alps."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Barbara Baths"],["alt=Barbarathermen"],["url=http:\/\/www.trier-info.de\/english\/barbara-baths-info"],["email="],["address="],["lat=49.750038"],["long=6.629704"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=large ruins of Roman baths"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Trier Imperial Baths"],["alt=Kaiserthermen"],["url=http:\/\/www.trier-info.de\/english\/imperial-baths-info"],["email="],["address=Weimarer Allee 2"],["lat=49.749608"],["long=6.642219"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Roman baths"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Roman amphitheater"],["alt="],["url="],["email="],["address=Bergstraße 45"],["lat=49.748027"],["long=6.649042"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=which used to host 20,000 spectators."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Forum Baths"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.trier-info.de\/english\/forum-baths-info"],["email="],["address="],["lat=49.75279"],["long=6.637646"],["directions="],["phone=+49 651 9941057"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Roman baths"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Basilica of Constantine"],["alt=Aula Palatina"],["url=http:\/\/ekkt.ekir.de\/trier\/884.0.html"],["email="],["address=Konstantinplatz"],["lat=49.753573"],["long=6.643378"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Roman palace basilica that was built by the emperor Constantine at the beginning of the 4th century."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Roman Bridge Trier"],["alt=Römerbrücke"],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat=49.751923"],["long=6.626512"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Over the river Mosel, nine bridge pillars date from the 2nd century AD"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Trier Cathedral"],["alt=Hohe Domkirche St. Peter zu Trier"],["url=http:\/\/www.dominformation.de\/internet-en\/nav\/add\/add70623-d64a-36f5-4abd-11d8bc1d2b31.htm"],["email="],["address=Liebfrauenstraße 12"],["lat=49.755431"],["long=6.643742"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=incorporates part of a church built by Emperor Constantine and contains the relic of the Holy Robe."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=St. Paulinus Church"],["alt=Sankt Paulinskirche"],["url=http:\/\/www.paulin-martin.de\/"],["email="],["address=Palmatiusstraße 4"],["lat=49.762528"],["long=6.652089"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=with its lovely Baroque interior."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Liebfrauenkirche"],["alt=Church of Our Lady"],["url=http:\/\/www.liebfrauen-trier.de\/"],["email="],["address=Liebfrauenstraße 2"],["lat=49.75586"],["long=6.643099"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=is one of the earliest ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Gothic architecture"],["Gothic"]]}," buildings in Germany."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=St. Matthias' Abbey"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.abteistmatthias.de\/"],["email="],["address=Matthiasstraße 85"],["lat=49.737988"],["long=6.631426"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Benedictine monastery, Romanesque basilica."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Rheinisches Landesmuseum, Trier"],["alt="],["url="],["email="],["address=Weimarer Allee 1"],["lat=49.751147"],["long=6.643785"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=one of the most important archeological museums in Germany"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Geburtshaus von Karl Marx"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.fes.de\/marx\/index_gr.html"],["email="],["address=Brückenstraße 10"],["lat=49.753864"],["long=6.635717"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content= is where Karl Marx was born, in 1818."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Judengasse"],["alt="],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat=49.757378"],["long=6.641255"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=a former Jewish Street that now houses different bars."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=old Jewish cemetery"],["alt=Jüdische Friedhöfe"],["url="],["email="],["address=Weidegasse"],["lat=49.748305"],["long=6.632442"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=From the 17th century."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Old Crane"],["alt=Alter Krahnen"],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat=49.756301"],["long=6.629052"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Harbour crane dating from 1413"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Customs Crane"],["alt=Zollkran"],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat=49.753923"],["long=6.628156"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=18th century crane"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Open air museum Roscheider Hof"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.roscheiderhof.de\/index.php\/en\/"],["email="],["address=Roscheiderhof 1"],["lat=49.705818"],["long=6.597429"],["directions=Konz"],["phone=+49 6501 92710"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=an ethnological museum of the Saar-Mosel region. About 5 km south from the city center."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Sankt Paulin BW 5.JPG"],["thumb"],["Interior of St. Paul (Sankt Paulin) Church"]]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Learn"]},"\n\nTrier hosts a ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.uni-trier.de University"]}," as well as a University of Applied Sciences (the so-called ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.fh-trier.de Fachhochschule"]},").\n\nThe Fachhochschule is in sight of the city. The first buildings were built in 1944 and were used by the Nazis to educate the next generation of soldiers. After the war, the complex was not officially used as a school. In the 1970's the University of Trier was refounded and used the buildings until a new university complex was built on the other side of the Mosel valley. Since then the Fachhochschule uses the complex.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Work"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Buy"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["Budget"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=Astarix"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.astarix-trier.de\/"],["email="],["address=Karl-Marx-Straße 11"],["lat=49.753019"],["long=6.634443"],["directions=next to the theater, in the south-west of the inner city"],["phone=+49 651 72239"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Inexpensive and tasty meals such as pizza (with your choice of toppings), casseroles, salads etc. can be found in the formerly student-owned"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=New Mintons"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.newmintons.de\/in-Trier\/Home.html"],["email="],["address=Jakobstraße 13"],["lat=49.757895"],["long=6.640232"],["directions= it's minutes away from the main square"],["phone=+49 651 9790265"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content= When visiting on a Tuesday be sure to check out ,they have schnitzelabend where you can order any schnitzel with fries and salad for just 5 euros between 6 and 10pm."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" There are many Kebab stores, located all over the city. The best you will find in the Judengasse, the Ke-Pasta."]},{"type":"*","value":[" There is a McDonalds and a SubWay in the market square and a Burger King near the main station."]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["Mid-range"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=Kartoffel Kiste"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.kistetrier.de"],["email="],["address=Fahrstraße 13"],["lat=49.753504"],["long=6.638901"],["directions="],["phone=+49 651 9790066"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=German dishes, every way you can server a potato."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["Splurge"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=Becker's"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.beckers-trier.de\/"],["email="],["address=Olewiger Straße 206"],["lat=49.743032"],["long=6.664859"],["directions="],["phone=+49 651 938080"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=is a two-star Michelin restaurant located in the Olewig area of Trier."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\n\nTrier lies at the heart of a famous wine region. In recent decades, vintners have added reds (especially Spätburgunder) and rosés to the traditional whites (especially Riesling). Apart from the standard wines and beers (Trier - ",{"type":"'''","value":["Löwenbräu"]},", Cologne - often ",{"type":"'''","value":["Gaffel Kölsch"]},", Bitburg - ",{"type":"'''","value":["Bitburger"]},"), one should definitely try ",{"type":"'''","value":["Viez"]},". Viez is a natural, refreshing apple wine, which many prefer with a splash of orange soda ",{"type":"'''","value":["Viez\/Limo"]}," or with half sparkling mineral water ",{"type":"'''","value":["Viez-Sprüdel"]},"because of the tartness. In October, many enjoy freshly pressed apple juice (",{"type":"'''","value":["süßen Viez"]},") or mixing this unfermented juice with half regular Viez. The drink is traditionally served in a white porcelain or stoneware mug holding .4 l.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Sleep"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Trier Kurfuerstliches Palais BW 1.JPG"],["thumb"],["Prince-Elector's Palace"]]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["Budget"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Youth hostel Trier"],["alt=Römerstadt- Jugendherberge Trier"],["url=http:\/\/www.diejugendherbergen.de\/die-jugendherbergen-auf-einen-blick\/trier\/portrait"],["email="],["address=An der Jugendherberge 4"],["lat=49.768086"],["long=6.640719"],["directions="],["phone=+49 651 146620"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price=about €20\/night"],["checkin="],["checkout="],["content=Directly on the banks of the Moselle."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Treviris camper parking"],["url="],["email="],["address=In Den Moselauen"],["lat=49.7419"],["long=06.62444"],["directions=Under Mosel bridge"],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["checkin="],["checkout="],["content=Big parking area. Showers, toilet. No power."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["Mid-range"]},"\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Blesius Garten"],["url=http:\/\/www.blesius-garten.de"],["email="],["address=Olewiger Straße 135"],["lat=49.743355"],["long=6.659836"],["directions="],["phone = +49 651-36060"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price=From €100"],["checkin="],["checkout="],["content=Very welcoming hotel, based in the Olewig area of Trier, has its own brewery on site. Rooms are well maintained, staff were friendly & helpful. About 1.5 miles outside of the city centre."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Casa Chiara"],["url=http:\/\/www.casa-chiara.de\/"],["email="],["address=Engelstraße 8"],["lat=49.76101"],["long=6.643594"],["directions="],["phone=+49-651-270730"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price=From €70"],["checkin="],["checkout="],["content=Around the corner from Porta Nigra, this is a solid 3-star hotel with vaguely Italian-style rooms and a sunny roofed garden for breakfast."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Hotel Frankenturm"],["url=http:\/\/www.hotel-frankenturm.de\/"],["email=frankenturm@t-online"],["address=Dietrichstrasse 3"],["lat=49.757115"],["long=6.639635"],["directions="],["phone = +49 651-978240"],["tollfree="],["fax=0651-9782449"],["hours="],["price=From €65"],["checkin="],["checkout="],["content= A boutique hotel in the Old City a block away from the Main Market. Twelve modern and distinctively furnished rooms above a charming restaurant. En suite bath for €20 extra."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Nells Park"],["url=http:\/\/www.nellsparkhotel.de\/"],["email="],["address=Dasbachstraße 12"],["lat=49.77083"],["long=6.669985"],["directions="],["phone=+49 651 14440"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price=From €100"],["checkin="],["checkout="],["content= About 2 miles out of Trier, easily accessible by bus, and as the name suggests, within a park. All rooms are individually decorated and in varying states of renovation (ask for a new one).  Parking was a bit tight, but plenty of parking on the road next to the hotel. Excellent food too."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["Splurge"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Stay safe"]},"\nTrier is a relatively safe city.  Standard travel safety applies\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Connect"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Cope"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Go next"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Luxembourg"]]}]},"\n\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["wikipedia:Trier"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["commons:category:Trier"]]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["geo"],["49.756667"],["6.641389"]]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["isPartOf"],["Moselle valley"]]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["outlinecity"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Dmoz:Regional\/Europe\/Germany\/States\/Rhineland-Palatinate\/Localities\/Trier\/"]]}]